\description{
Estimates three networks from ESM/EMA panel data, matching
validated \code{mlVAR::mlVAR()} configurations at machine precision: (1) a directed
temporal network of fixed-effect lagged regression coefficients, (2)
an undirected contemporaneous network of partial correlations among
residuals, and (3) an undirected between-subjects network of partial
correlations derived from the person-mean fixed effects.
}
\details{
The algorithm follows mlVAR's lmer pipeline exactly:
\enumerate{
\item Drop rows with NA in id/day/beep and optionally grand-mean
standardize each variable.
\item Expand the per-(id, day) beep grid and right-join original
values, producing the augmented panel (\code{augData}).
\item Add within-person lagged predictors (\verb{L1_*}) and person-mean
predictors (\verb{PM_*}).
\item For each outcome variable fit
\code{lmer(y ~ within + between-except-own-PM + (1 | id))} with
\code{REML = FALSE}. Collect the fixed-effect temporal matrix \code{B},
between-effect matrix \code{Gamma}, random-intercept SDs (\code{mu_SD}),
and lmer residual SDs.
\item Contemporaneous network:
\code{cor2pcor(D \%*\% cov2cor(cor(resid)) \%*\% D)}.
\item Between-subjects network:
\code{cor2pcor(pseudoinverse(forcePositive(D (I - Gamma))))}.
}

The committed oracle matrix validates fixed temporal/contemporaneous \code{lmer}
fits at lags 1 and 1+2, preprocessing controls (\code{scale}, \code{scaleWithin},
\code{compareToLags}, \code{trueMeans}, and position detrending), and lag-1
\code{estimator = "lm"}, \code{temporal = "unique"} fits across every supported
contemporaneous structure. Other configurations carry a narrower
declaration available through \code{\link[=equivalence]{equivalence()}}.
}
\section{Observation keys}{

When \code{beep} is supplied, every complete \verb{(id, day, beep)} key (or \verb{(id, beep)} when \code{day = NULL}) must be unique. Duplicate keys often indicate that
a study-period/session column was lost during data conversion. Because
upstream join behavior is row-order dependent in that case, \code{fit_mlvar()}
errors and asks you to resolve or explicitly deduplicate the source data.
}

